<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">By Archetype The 23rd</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Written: 13 April 2003 7:49PM EST</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<br>
It seems the Apollo sector likes to repeat history.  Sometimes outsiders looking in like to imagine they learn their lessons.  That they mature and grow from each experience.  Today I was taking my usual dosage of medication when I was sent an AIM message from a respectable micronationalist.  Well known through out the sector and who's advice I always file away for future reference.  Today however he sent me a rather out of character message I wont quote his name but guess who he is as you will.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Micronationalist: ROFLMAO<br>
Archetype2357: ?<br>
Micronationalist: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub37.ezboard.com/frepublicofdelvenusfrm41.showMessage?topicID=168.topic">pub37.ezboard.com/frepubl...=168.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->  the hypocracy never ends!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The above link lead me to this post.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>After some thought, I've decided to reopen the MCS, I've decided to put in place some ideas from the rebirth project and such. A panel of about 5 shall be created, taken from representatives from the nations on the map. The members will rotate about every 2 months or so. And MUST remain active on the panel, else be replaced.<br>
<br>
As well, the MCS map will no longer be formally called Micras, it shall have no designation aside from the traditional &quot;MCS map&quot;.<br>
<br>
I've informed my cartographers, through Sirithil, that I would like the next map update restarted. So hopefully that will be out around the 20th.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Which to the casual observer is not anything out of the ordinary.  An organization after careful thought realizes they made a mistake in closing and decide to correct it by opening up again.  That seems reasonable doesn't it?  Well to a more educated observer whom has interacted with the personalities of this sector it is a classic apollo move.  They never are able to let a good thing die but always try to revive it.  <br>
<br>
A quote by Scott Siskind owner of the Apollo Skyline, and Co-owner of the Micronational Cartography Society states.  &quot;Micras existed, it had a good run, we all enjoyed it, and now unfortunate circumstances have compelled us to move on. We will. We always have.&quot;   By this statement one would assume we are now going to move on to new projects, new worlds, and new beginnings.<br>
<br>
However we aren't dealing with normal personalities.  It is the apollo tradition and ways to not stick to your decisions and strive forward.  It is however tradition to backtrack and try the same thing twice, three times, and in cases like Audentior.. one to many times.  That is no disrespect to Audentior, just part of apollo reality. <br>
<br>
A few more examples of this tradition is cases like Philip Locke.  Who has to date I believe betrayed, or damaged a nation he has belonged too at least (this is a kind number) four times.  However in classic tradition each time people have after a few weeks once again returned to normal procedure with him.  Each time telling me that they believed he had changed.. guess what some people just don't.  <br>
<br>
It is also disheartening to see an organization like The MCS whom closed down over disputes of not being neutral in a decision, hire on board prior to that decision &quot;Sirithil Nos Feanor.&quot; Whom is well known for her fascist views and actions in the past.  However we can assume they have grown up correct and what do something like that again?  Even though Sirithil has performed two major acts of cruelity.<br>
<br>
The Classic Apollo Tradition may not be repeating the past, but simply forgetting it.  This is possibly what is occuring, people forget they where betrayed.  Forget that everytime they do ____ it fails.  So constantly repeat it, it may even be a clincal disorder.  Some speculate it should be called Apollo Syndrome.  <br>
<br>
Why you ask may I write this article? To spread anti-apollo propaganda right? To be prejudiced? Hardly I have an alterior motive and allow me to share it with you.  By this current mentality people want &quot;Menelmacar to make up and normalize relations.&quot;  and forget the past.  In the real world if a member of a government wanted to &quot;Just forget&quot; what traitors did, he'd probably be at the very least suspected of conspiracy.  <br>
<br>
This isn't paranoid thinking to all those who wish to use that as a scapegoat for my opinions.  That is a reality of the real world that so many wish to ignore in micronations.  If you want to simulate try simulating, I don't know sticking to your principles.  People with principles are hard to come by these days, try being one of the elite and hold people accountable for their actions.  Don't fall victim to The Syndrome. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.thebananamovement.tk" target="top">Jekh dilo kerel but dile hai but dile keren dilimata</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bmenelmacar.showUserPublicProfile?gid=archetype23>Archetype23</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://collectiveunconscious.port5.com/Animations/Roma.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 4/13/03 7:07:52 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm41.showPrevMessage?topicID=5.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm41.showNextMessage?topicID=5.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm41.emailToFriend?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm41.threadControl?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/posticons/techops.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fmenelmacarfrm41.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies